</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/23448292-sue-jarvi">Sue Jarvi</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    This is one of the things that bothers me about this book. It's basically saying it's OK to do whatever it takes (including killing someone) to get wh<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    This is one of the things that bothers me about this book. It's basically saying it's OK to do whatever it takes (including killing someone) to get what you want in life and if you're outstanding enough in your field, others will even cover for you. It reminds me of some professional athletes who think they can do whatever they want because they're rich and famous. It seems to be perpetuating that mindset.<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
