</a><br><br>Then a death happens. So many twisty turns. That my silly 'read too many of these type books' self figured out. <br><br> Abbott's writing did keep me reading. I loved seeing all the dark sides of all these hyper-sorta nutty people. From my personal viewpoint I knew that this was a glimpse into a life that I just can't imagine, because I just don't know if I have enough of that pageant mom mentality. <br><a href="http://www.freeimagehosting.net/commercial-photography/" rel="nofollow noopener">
